params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.response_type
params.description: The type of response. This may indicate that an action must be taken by the client when the response is received.

params.name: data.additions
params.description: A set of entries to add to a local threat type's list.

params.name: data.removals
params.description: A set of entries to remove from a local threat type's list. This field may be empty.

params.name: data.checksum
params.description: The expected SHA256 hash of the client state; that is, of the sorted list of all hashes present in the database after applying the provided diff. If the client state doesn't match the expected state, the client must disregard this diff and retry later.

params.name: data.recommended_next_diff
params.description: The soonest the client should wait before issuing any diff request. Querying sooner is unlikely to produce a meaningful diff. Waiting longer is acceptable considering the use case. If this field is not set clients may update as soon as they want.
